alab 2020]]''\n*''[[The Secret Files of the Spy Dogs]]''\n*''[[Shirt Tales]]''\n*''[[Silverhawks]]''\n*''[[Sk8 (TV series)|Sk8]]''\n*''[[Skysurfer Strike Force]]''\n*''[[The Smurfs (Hanna-Barbera series)|The Smurfs]]''\n*''[[Space Ace]]''\n*''[[Space Ghost]]''\n*''[[Star Street: The Adventures of the Star Kids]]''\n*''[[The Super Globetrotters]]''\n*''[[Super Friends]]''\n*''[[Superhuman Samurai Syber-Squad]]''\n*''[[Superman: The Animated Series]]''\n*''[[Sylvanian Families (1987 TV series)|Sylvanian Families]]''\n*''[[Tabaluga (TV series)|Tabaluga]]''\n*''[[Tales from the Neverending Story]]''\n*''[[Tattooed Teenage Alien Fighters from Beverly Hills]]''\n*''[[Taz-Mania]]''\n*''[[Alberto y Lost Trios Paranoias|Teach Yourself Gibberish]]''\n*''[[Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (1987 TV series)|Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles]]''\n*''[[Three's Company]]''\n*''[[Thundarr the Barbarian]]''\n*''[[ThunderCats (1985 TV series)|ThunderCats]]''\n*''[[Thunderstone (TV series)|Thunderstone]]''\n*''[[Tiny Toon Adventures]]''\n*''[[The Tofus]]''\n*''[[Tom and Jerry]]''\n*''[[Tom & Jerry Kids]]''\n*''[[The Sylvester & Tweety Mysteries]]''\n*''[[The Tomorrow People (1992 TV series)|The Tomorrow People]]''\n*''[[Top Cat]]''\n*''Toyota World of Wildlife''\n*''[[Turbo Teen]]''\n*''[[The Tribe (1999 TV series)|The Tribe]]''\n*''[[Twipsy]]''\n*''[[Ultraforce (comics)|Ultraforce]]''\n*''[[Ultraman]]''\n*''[[Valley of the Dinosaurs]]''\n*''Wakey Wakey''\n*''[[A Walk In Your Shoes]]''\n*''[[Walter Melon (TV series)|Walter Melon]]''\n*''[[Waynehead]]''\n*''[[The What a Cartoon! Show]]''\n*''[[What's with Andy?]]''\n*''[[Wheelie and the Chopper Bunch]]''\n*''[[Where's Waldo? (TV series)|Where's Wally?]]''\n*''[[The Why Why Family]]''\n*''Wicked!''\n*''[[Widget (TV series)|Widget the World Watcher]]''\n*''[[Wildfire (1986 TV series)|Wildfire]]''\n*''[[The Wizard of Oz (TV series)|The Wizard of Oz]]''\n*''[[Wacky Races (1968 TV series)|Wacky Races]]''\n*''[[WKRP in Cincinnati]]''\n*''[[Women of the House]]''\n*''[[Woofer & Wimper: Dog Detectives]]''\n*''[[Wunschpunsch]]''\n*''[[Yogi Bear]]''\n*''[[Yogi's Space Race]]''\n*''[[Yogi's Treasure Hunt]]''\n*''[[Young Robin Hood]]''\n*''[[Yo, Yogi!]]''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090416030949/http://orbit.net/channels.aspx?ch=FC Official Site] (Wayback Machine archive)\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090416080425/http://www.orbit.net/ Orbit's Official Site] (Wayback Machine archive)\n\n[[Category:Arab media]]\n[[Category:Children's television networks]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 1994]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 1995]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations disestablished in 2000]]\n[[Category:Television stations in Chile]]\n[[Category:Television stations in the Middle East and North Africa]]\n[[Category:Media in Chile]]\n[[Category:Chilean television networks]]\n[[Category:1995 establishments in Chile]]\n[[Category:2000 disestablishments in Chile]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language television stations]]\n", "text_old": "{{more references|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox television channel\n|name           = Fun Channel\n|logofile       =\n|logosize       =\n|launch         = 1994 (Middle East)<br>18 June 1995 (Chile)\n|closed date    = 2000 (Chile)\n|picture format =\n|country        = Middle East<br>Chile\n|owner          = [[Orbit Network]]\n|slogan         =\n|broadcast area = Middle East<br>Chile\n|language       = [[Arabic language|Arabic]]<br>[[Spanish language|Spanish]]\n|headquarters   =\n}}\n\n'''Fun Channel''' is a [[Middle Eastern]] television channel owned by the [[Orbit Network]]. Fun Channel contains cartoons for children from early morning to evening such as ''[[The Why Why Family]]'' and ''[[Dennis the Menace (1986 TV series)|Dennis the Menace]]''. From late night to early morning, it contains shows for pre-teens and older such as ''[[California Dreams]]'' and ''[[Hang Time (TV series)|Hang Time]]''.\n\nBetween 2005 and 2010, it used to simulcast [[Jetix Play]].\n== History ==\nLaunched in 1994, Fun Channel broadcasts family-friendly entertainment, including animated and live action shows. On April 14, 2004 Fun Channel changed its logo and added more animated shows to its lineup. Fun Channel primarily airs in [[Kuwait]] and the [[United Arab Emirates]], although it was also available in Chile with the network and programming dubbed into Spanish.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tiftongazette.com/news/local_news/fun-channel-expanding-across-south-georgia/article_e571d130-8139-53d7-8622-d416d3c8c895.html|title=Fun Channel expanding across South Georgia|last=Beckham|first=Chris|website=The Tifton Gazette|language=en|access-date=2019-07-02}}</ref> The Chilean version of the Fun Channel was launched on June 18, 1995 and closed down in 2000.\n\n== List of programmes ==\n*''[[2030 CE]]''\n*''[[The 3 Friends and Jerry]]''\n*''[[Ace Ventura: Pet Detective (TV series)|Ace Ventura: Pet Detective]]''\n*''[[The Addams Family (1992 TV series)|The Addams Family]]''\n*''[[Adventures in Odyssey]]''\n*''[[The Adventures of Don Coyote and Sancho Panda]]''\n*''[[The Adventures of Gulliver]]''\n*''[[The Adventures of Shirley Holmes]]''\n*''[[The Adventures of Swiss Family Robinson]]''\n*''[[The Adventures of the Black Stallion]]''\n*''[[The Adventures of the Bush Patrol]]''\n*''[[The Adventures of the Little Prince (TV series)|The Adventures of the Little Prince]]''\n*''[[The Adventures of Tintin (TV series)|The Adventures of Tintin]]''\n*''[[ALF: The Animated Series]]''\n*''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks (1983 TV series)|Alvin and the Chipmunks]]''\n*''[[Angelina Ballerina (TV series)|Angelina Ballerina]]''\n*''[[Animal Ark]]''\n*''[[Animaniacs]]''\n*''Animated Classic Showcase''\n*''[[Anthony Ant]]''\n*''[[The Anti-Gravity Room]]''\n*''[[Archibald the Koala]]''\n*''[[Around the World in 80 Dreams]]''\n*''[[Art Attack]]''\n*''[[Atom Ant]]''\n*''[[A.J.'s Time Trave