{"title_page": "Sipra", "text_new": "{| class=\"toccolours\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"2\" style=\"float: right; margin: 0 0 1em 1em; width: 250px; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"margin-left: inherit; background:#FFC0CB; text-align:center; font-size: medium;\" |'''Sipra''' \n|- align=\"center\"\n|- style=\"vertical-align: top;\"\n| '''Distribution'''\n| [[Punjab (Pakistan)]] \n|- style=\"vertical-align: top;\"\n| '''Descended from:'''\n| \n|- style=\"vertical-align: top;\"\n| '''Branches:'''\n| Gill Jat\n|- style=\"vertical-align: top;\"\n| '''Religion'''\n| [[Islam]], [[Hindu]], [[Sikhs]]\n|- style=\"vertical-align: top;\"\n| '''Languages'''\n| [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]],Saraiki,Sindi,Balochi \n|- style=\"vertical-align: top;\"\n| '''Surnames:'''\n| Sipra\n|- style=\"vertical-align: top;\"\n<!--| colspan=2 | <small>{{{footnotes}}}</small> -->\n|}\n'''Sipra''' (also known as '''Sapra''') is a tribe in the [[Punjab region]] of [[Pakistan]] and [[India]]. Sipra is a [[Muslim Jat|Muslim]], [[Hindu]], [[Sikh]] tribe<ref name=\"Rose\">''A Glossary of the Tribes and Castes of Punjab and the North West Frontier Province'';  Vol. II, p. 881; by Horace Arthur Rose</ref> found mainly in the western districts of [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]] in [[Pakistan]].<ref>''Punjabi Musalmans''; by J. M. Wikely; p. 112</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThe Sipra are a sub-division of the [[Jat Muslim|Jat]]. It means 'river'. While the Sapra is used by Hindus and Sikhs. <ref>''A Glossary of the Tribes & Castes of Punjab'' by [[Horace Rose|H. A. Rose]]</ref>\n\n== Location ==\nThe tribe is chiefly found along the banks of [[Chenab]] , [[Jhelum]] and [[Indus]] River, in the districts of [[Gujrat City|Gujrat]], [[Mandi Bahauddin]], [[Sargodha]], [[Jhelum District|Jhelum]], [[Jhang]], [[Gujranwala]], [[Hafizabad]], [[Sheikhpura]], [[Kasur]], [[Okara District|Okara]],  [[Faisalabad]], [[Sahiwal]], [[Chichawatni]], [[Mian Channu]], [[Vehari]], [[Chiniot]],[[Chak Number 203,211,199,198 JB, Tehsil Bhowana]], [[Toba Tek Singh|Gojra]], [[Chak Number 305/JB Mansoorwali]], [[Bahawalpur]], [[Multan]], [[Muzzaffargarh]], [[Noor Shah]], [[Chak Number 522/TDA]], [[Chak Number 524/TDA]], [[Kot Addu]],[[Layyah]], [[Khanewal]], [[Rahim Yar Khan]], [[Rajanpur]], [[Kharian]], [[Kamalia Tehsil|Kamalia]], [[Tandlianwala]], [[Ahmadpur East]], [[Muridke]], [[Balkassar]], [[Kabirwala]], Mahmumwali, Changa Manga,  [[Narang Syedan]], [[Sikriala]] and [[Waryam Wala Station]], [[Mamoo kanjan]].\n\nAlso in [[Sindh]] in [[Karachi]],Ghotki And in Balochistan Jhal Magsi\n\n==Notable people==\n<!---\u2666\u2666\u2666\u2666 Only add a person to this list if they already have their own article on the English Wikipedia \u2666\u2666\u2666\u2666---> \n<!---\u2666\u2666\u2666\u2666 Provide a reference from a reliable source to show the person is a Sipra\u2666\u2666\u2666\u2666---> \n*   [[Haq Nawaz Jhangvi]], (Ex MNA) {{cn|date=January 2020}}\n*   [[Masroor Nawaz Jhangvi]], (Ex MPA) {{cn|date=March 2020}}\n*   [[Moeen Nizami]], poet, writer and scholar from [[Sargodha]] {{cn|date=January 2020}}\n*   [[Saqlain Anwar Sipra]], (Ex MPA) {{cn|date=January 2020}}\n<!---\u2666\u2666\u2666\u2666 Only add a person to this list if they already have their own article on the English Wikipedia \u2666\u2666\u2666\u2666---> \n<!---\u2666\u2666\u2666\u2666 Provide a reference from a reliable source to show the person is a Sipra\u2666\u2666\u2666\u2666--->\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Muslim communities of Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Social groups of Punjab, Pakistan]]\n\n\n{{Pakistan-ethno-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{| class=\"toccolours\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"2\" style=\"float: right; margin: 0 0 1em 1em; width: 250px; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"margin-left: inherit; background:#FFC0CB; text-align:center; font-size: medium;\" |'''Sipra''' \n|- align=\"center\"\n|- style=\"